        "type": "process-procedure",
        "title": "ato-in-a-pipeline CI/CD pipeline",
        "description": "The secure software delivery pipeline (SAST, secrets scanning, vulnerability scanning, SBOM, signing, Kyverno admission policy, and drift detection) defined in this repository.",
        "control-implementations": [
          {
            "uuid": "a6b67aff-b0ec-53f3-9b34-fa4a4b5e4223",
            "source": "https://csrc.nist.gov/extensions/nvd/nist-sp-800-53r5-resolved-profile-catalog.json",
            "description": "NIST 800-53 rev5 controls implemented by the ato-in-a-pipeline CI/CD pipeline",
            "implemented-requirements": [
              {
                "uuid": "aad8df66-2379-52c8-9456-f6031d553d5f",
                "control-id": "cm-2",
                "description": "The LocalStack infra baseline (VPC, subnet, internet gateway, route table, security group, S3 bucket, DynamoDB lock table) is codified in Terraform, not manually configured. The OS-level STIG baseline is likewise codified as an idempotent Ansible role rather than a one-time image-build fix, re-applied and re-verified against a running container on demand (Phase 8).",
                "links": [
                  {
                    "href": "terraform/main.tf",
                    "rel": "evidence",
                    "text": "terraform/main.tf"
                  },
                  {
                    "href": "ansible/roles/stig_hardening/tasks/main.yml",
                    "rel": "evidence",
                    "text": "ansible/roles/stig_hardening/tasks/main.yml"
                  },
                  {
                    "href": "docs/evidence/phase8-harden-idempotency.txt",
                    "rel": "evidence",
                    "text": "idempotency evidence"
                  },
                  {
                    "href": "docs/adr/0007-ansible-configuration-management.md",
                    "rel": "evidence",
                    "text": "ADR 0007"
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "uuid": "9267e054-1dd5-526f-b8a4-514ba60169af",
                "control-id": "cm-3",
                "description": "Every infra change runs `terraform fmt`/`validate`/`plan` in CI before it can merge; plan output is posted as a reviewable artifact.",
                "links": [
                  {
                    "href": ".github/workflows/pipeline.yml#L88-L102",
                    "rel": "evidence",
                    "text": ".github/workflows/pipeline.yml#L88-L102"
                  },
                  {
                    "href": "docs/adr/0004-terraform-localstack-scope.md",
                    "rel": "evidence",
                    "text": "ADR 0004"
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "uuid": "668dc17f-6bae-575f-97ea-7fc39ba216d9",
                "control-id": "cm-6",
                "description": "The UBI9 base image is remediated against the RHEL9 DISA STIG profile (umask policy, root shell-init file permissions, tmpfiles override) at image-build time. Phase 8 re-expresses the same four settings as idempotent Ansible tasks that apply and verify them against a running container, proving the baseline isn't just a one-shot Dockerfile artifact; the same three findings ADR 0003 documents as structurally out of scope for any container (PAM/su, FIPS kernel mode, DNS resolv.conf) remain out of scope at runtime for the same reasons.",
                "links": [
                  {
                    "href": "Dockerfile#L28-L42",
                    "rel": "evidence",
                    "text": "Dockerfile#L28-L42"
                  },
                  {
                    "href": "docs/evidence/phase2-openscap-stig-before.html",
                    "rel": "evidence",
                    "text": "before OpenSCAP report"
                  },
                  {
                    "href": "docs/evidence/phase2-openscap-stig-after.html",
                    "rel": "evidence",
                    "text": "after OpenSCAP report"
                  },
